.TH "t3_set_reg_field" 9 "t3_set_reg_field" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t3_set_reg_field \- set a register field to a value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" t3_set_reg_field
.BI "(struct adapter *adapter "  ","
.BI "unsigned int addr "  ","
.BI "u32 mask "  ","
.BI "u32 val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adapter" 12
the adapter to program
.IP "addr" 12
the register address
.IP "mask" 12
specifies the portion of the register to modify
.IP "val" 12
the new value for the register field

Sets a register field specified by the supplied mask to the
given value.
